Soultion was built with:
- Visual Studio 2010; Visual Studio Express, which is free, might also work (http://www.microsoft.com/express)
- MVC 3 Tools Update (http://www.microsoft.com/download/en/details.aspx?id=1491)
- NuGet for package management (http://nuget.org/)
- Many NuGet packages inlcuded in the solution under the Packages folder
- ReSharper for code refactoring and cleanup (http://www.jetbrains.com/resharper/)

Testing was done with:
- NUnit for decorating classes and methods as tests (http://www.nunit.org/)
- Moq for object mocking (http://code.google.com/p/moq/)
- ReSharper as a test runner, although NUnit also has a built in test runner (http://www.jetbrains.com/resharper/)

Database was done with:
- SQL Server Express (http://www.microsoft.com/sqlserver/en/us/editions/express.aspx)

To install and run locally:
- Download and unzip all code from GitHub (https://github.com/techthrowdown/Rails-vs-.NET/tree/master/ASP.NET%20MVC)
- Install and setup SQL Server Express using Windows Authentication.  The connection string in the project assumes .\EXPRESS will resolve as the instance name.  If you need to change this, you can change the connection string in the Web.config file in the ProductDevelopment.Web folder.
- Install Visual Studio 2010 or Visual Studio Express
- Open the solution file "ProductDevelopment.sln" with Visual Studio
- Press F5 to build and run the project using your local database and development web server